The Katsina North senatorial candidate of the All Progressives Congress, APC, Ahmad Baba Kaita was defeated at President Muhammadu Buhari’s polling unit, at the Sarkin Yara Ward A, Kofa Baru polling unit (03), Gidan Niyam in Daura local government area of Katsina state. The polling unit was won by Accord Party. Presiding officer, a corp member, Aliyu Abdullahi announced that APC’s candidate, Ahmad Baba Kaita polled 247, Mani Nasarawa (PDP) got 2 and Mohammed Lawal Nalado of the Accord Party 262. However, President Buhari won the presidential election at the unit, polling 523 votes, while Atiku Abubakar of the Peoples Democratic Party recorded 3 votes.  APC Leads in Daura, Bauchi Senatorial By-elections How APC won Katsina, Bauchi by-elections Nigeria decides today